(6815, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_001', 'Notification Name'),
(6816, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_001_DESCR', 'This is the name of the notification which briefly describes its nature. Notification Name is not included in the body of the notification e-mail. It is only used to identify the notification.<br>This field is required.'),
(6817, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_002', 'E-Mail Subject'),
(6818, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_002_DESCR', 'This is the subject of the notification e-mail. The E-Mail Subject is included in the e-mail and is visible to the recipient.<br><br>The format {InfoTag} is supported in the <nobr>E-mail</nobr> Subject. For example, if the <nobr>E-mail</nobr> Subject contains the tag {OrderID}, the recipient will see an actual ID of his/her order. The list of info tags supported in the <nobr>E-mail</nobr> Subject is provided in the section <nobr>E-mail</nobr> Body.'),
(6819, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_003', 'Send Mail on Action'),
(6820, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_003_DESCR', 'This setting is used to control what triggers notifications.<br><br> When ''Order Status Changed'' or ''Payment Status Changed'' is selected, you can additionally select which status must be changed to cause a notification to be sent.'),
(6821, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_005', 'Send to'),
(6822, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_006', 'Send from'),
(6823, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_007', 'Active'),
(6824, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_007_DESCR', 'This setting displays the status of the notification <nobr>e-mail.</nobr> Select the checkbox to activate this notification. If you don''t want to send out notifications of this type, clear the checkbox.'),
(6825, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_008', 'E-Mail Body'),
(6826, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_008_DESCR', 'This is the body of the notification e-mail. The e-mail body may contain info tags which are used to display various pieces of information.<br><br> For example, if the E-Mail Body contains the tag {OrderID}, the recipient will see an actual ID of his/her order in the e-mail. The list of info tags supported in the E-Mail Body is provided in the section Available Info Tags.<br><br> In particular, the E-Mail Body can contain cyclic block tags. For instance, the {OrderContentBlock} tag displays the full list of products included in an order. The template for displaying the product list is defined in the section Block Tag Templates. To add a tag, select it and click the Left button.'),
(6827, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_009', 'Available Info Tags'),
(6828, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_009_DESCR', 'This defines the list of info tags. Tag names are used to identify what kind of information the tag displays. For example, the {CustomerFirstname} tag added to the e-mail body will be actually displayed as the customer''s first name.<br><br> NOTE about the tag {OrderTax}: This tag displays both the textual information with tax names and the tax amounts. Tax names are defined in Store Settings >> Taxes.'),
(6829, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_0091', 'Available Tags'),
(6830, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_0091_DESCR', 'The list of tags that can be used in the corresponding block tag. To move an info tag, select it and click the Left button.'),
(6831, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_010', 'Available Block Tags'),
(6832, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_010_DESCR', 'This is the list of Block Tags available.<br><br>Block tags allow you to display cyclic information or information consisting of several info tags.<br><br>For example, {OrderContentBlock} can be used to display information about the contents of an order. The template used to display the contents is defined in the section Block Tag Templates.'),
(6833, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_013', 'Available Senders'),
(6834, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_013_DESCR', 'This is the list of available senders. The contents of the list are based on the settings selected on Store Configuration >> Store Owner''s Profile. Choose one sender from the list of available senders.'),
(6835, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_014', 'Independent Sender'),
(6836, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_014_DESCR', 'This lets you enter the name of an independent sender.<br><br> Use the following format:<br><br> ''Name &lt;abc@xyzcompany.com&gt;''<br><br> where ''Name'' is the sender''s name and ''abc@xyzcompany.com'' is the sender''s e-mail address.'),
(6837, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_015', 'Target Recipients'),
(6838, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_015_DESCR', 'This is the list of recipients to whom notifications are sent.<br><br>To add a recipient to the list, select the appropriate recipient''s name in the list of Available Recipients and click the Left button. The selected recipient will be included into the list. To remove a recipient from the list, select the recipient''s name are click the Right button.'),
(6839, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_016', 'Available Recipients'),
(6840, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_016_DESCR', 'This is the list of all available recipients.<br><br>The contents of the list are based on settings selected on Store Configuration >> Store Owner''s Profile.<br><br>To be able to send notifications to a recipient, his/her name must be added to the list of Target Recipients. Select the recipient''s name and click the Left button to include the recipient into the list of Target Recipients.'''),
(6841, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_017', 'Independent Recipient'),
(6842, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_017_DESCR', 'This allows you to enter the name and e-mail address of an independent recipient.<br><br> Use the following format:<br><br> ''Name &lt;abc@xyzcompany.com&gt;''<br><br> where ''Name'' is the recipient''s name and ''abc@xyzcompany.com'' is the recipient''s e-mail address.<br><br> Enter the name and e-mail address for an independent recipient and click the Left button. The e-mail address will be included into the list of Target Recipients to whom the notification will be sent.'),
(6843, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_018', 'Block Tag Templates'),
(6844, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_019', 'Block tag'),
(6845, 'NTFCTN', 'NTFCTN_INFO_FIELD_019_DESCR', '{OrderContentBlock} is a cyclic tag. This means that if this tag''s template looks like:<br>{ProductID}<br>{ProductName}<br><br>then, if the order consists of three products, the following information will be displayed:<br><br>Product ID 1<br>Product Name 1<br><br>Product ID 2<br>Product Name 2<br><br>Product ID 3<br>Product Name 3.<br><br>The list of tags used in this block tag is given in the section Available Tags located to the right. To move an info tag, select it and click the Left button.'),
